<h2 class="sectionedit1"><a name="type_specifiers" id="type_specifiers">Type specifiers</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

</div>
<!-- EDIT1 SECTION "Type specifiers" [1-26] -->
<h3 class="sectionedit2"><a name="constness" id="constness">Constness</a></h3>
<div class="level3">
<ul>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> <code><strong>const</strong></code> - declares the intent that the variable should not be modified. Attempt to do that results in undefined behavior. On most of the compilers it is compile-time error.</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> <code><strong>mutable</strong></code> - declares the intent that a member of a class does not affect the externally visible state of a class. <code>mutable</code> members can be modified in <code>const</code> classes.</div>
</li>
</ul>

